Steps to Reproduce:

Syntax highlighting for keywords like noexcept and delete is not working as shown in the screenshot with the following code:

#include <iostream>

class Myclass
{
public:
    Myclass()
        : x(), y(),
        z()
    {
    }

    Myclass(const Myclass&) noexcept = delete;
    void print() { std::cout << 1 << std::endl; }

private:
    int x;
    int y;
    int z;
};

1. It is observed that this issue occurs when the constructor initializer list is spread over more than a line.
2. Issue exists for all themes and when all extensions are disabled as well
3. Code works and tested with g++
